1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. e3 O-O 6. Nf3 Nbd7
{ The most neutral move for Black, which was named after Rubinstein. The most important rationale for this move is that Black doesn't know yet how he wants to finish his development. He keeps open the option of the manoeuvre ...Rf8-e8 and ...Nd7-f8, which is typical for this variation. With the text move, White is immediately questioned as to how he should bring his other pieces into play. }
7. Rc1
