{ With this move - also typical for the Ragozin - Black puts pressure on White's center. }
6. Bg5
{ Of course, White plays this counterpin, which prevents ...Nxe4. He's ready for e4-e5 and Bxc4. }
6... c5 7. Bxc4
{ This is the modern approach. White continues his development apace, hoping to make threats against Black's king in turn.   The critical variation now continues: }
