{ The possibility of   18...Ba6  was indicated by Ftacnik, and in spite of the further weakening of c6, I suspect Black should have done this and traded off his bad bishop. }
4. Qc2
{ Karpov is preparing the eventual central pawn thrust very carefully.  Again, the possibility of   19.e4  can be considered, but it doesnt give the desired results. After  dxe4  20.Nxe4  , Black has the answer  Qa3 !  and his position holds firm.  Not, though,   20...Qf4  due to  21.g3 !  Qb8  22.Bc4  . }
4... g6 5. e4 { The time is now ripe. } 5... dxe4 6. Nxe4 Qf4 7. Bc4
{ This is the idea. Blacks 19^th move turned his g-pawn into a potential target. }
*

