1... Bg6 2. Ke1 Nc8
{ Exploiting these kinds of advantages is right up Petrosians street. This knight goes to a new blockade square on d6. }
3. Rdf2 Rf7 4. Kd2 Nd6 { Black is clearly better by now. } 5. Nf5+ Bxf5
{ Obviously, he gives the bishop as it was the worse of the two minor pieces. }
6. exf5 c4 { In order to win, Black still needs to manage to open a-line. } 7.
Rb1 b5 { Very well timed. } 8. b4
